2026, 1st Revision CopyClaw Software License
An abbreviation for the CopyClaw Software License, like ©, is the "Lobster Emoji 🦞"; Example: Ardosoft Hello 🦞
Party 1 is the developer of the software. Party 2 is the user of the software distributed by Party 1 under the CopyClaw Software License.
When this license is used, the user of said license must classify in this license whether this is a Type C or Type N version of the CopyClaw Software License.
As a quick classification, Type C is generally considered more "Open" while Type N is more proprietary, It is up to the user to read both types to decide how they distribute their software.
You can classify it here: {Type ?} — Replace the "?" with the letter C or N depending on which version you use.
The following clauses are Type C:

General:

Party 1 may not charge currency or a subscription of any kind in order for party 2 to use their software.

Party 2 may:
Fork
Contribute
Redistribute (Independently); Meaning you may only redistribute as a individual but not as a corporation

But not:
Redistribute software originally licensed under CopyClaw Software License with a different license.

The following clauses are Type N:

General:

Party 1 may charge a subscription or currency for Party 2 to use their software.

Party 2 may:
Redistribute (Independently); Meaning you may only redistribute as a individual but not as a corporation
Contribute

But not:
Redistribute software originally licensed under CopyClaw Software License with a different license.

In both type C and N:

The source code may be viewed at any time from all parties
The software is provided as is and party 1 is not liable for any damages the software may cause to party 2's hardware or operating system.

If the 1st or 2nd party violates this license:

Their access to any software with the CopyClaw license is revoked permanently but not irrevocably.
